<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,437,986]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,437,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[417,502,437,462]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Deione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[417,502,437,462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Deione</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[724,858,437,462]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Chorizopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[724,858,437,462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Chorizopes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration, but it differs from the latter by the following features: cephalic region narrower than thoracic region and slightly elevated (wider and extremely elevated in 
<taxonomicName box="[286,419,512,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Chorizopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[286,419,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Chorizopes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); abdomen having two pairs of vertically arranged posterior lateral humps (one pair of lateral humps and one pair of median humps in 
<taxonomicName box="[727,863,549,574]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Chorizopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[727,863,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Chorizopes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); male tibia II extremely enlarged, with several large macrosetae (unmodified in 
<taxonomicName box="[538,671,586,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Chorizopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[538,671,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Chorizopes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); chelicerae with pro- and retromaginal teeth (only on promargin in 
<taxonomicName box="[181,314,624,649]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Chorizopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,314,624,649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Chorizopes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and absence of paramedian apophysis (present in 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1054,624,649]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Chorizopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[921,1054,624,649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Chorizopes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,437,986]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,661,687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Description.</emphasis>
Total length: 
<number box="[516,628,661,687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" value="5.1" valueMax="6.25" valueMin="3.95">3.95-6.25</number>
(female), 
<number box="[751,802,661,687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" value="3.45">3.45</number>
-4.00 (male). Carapace longer than wide, dark brown, covered with thin setae, cervical groove obvious, cephalic region slightly elevated (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1264,698,724]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1730,1754]" captionTargetBox="[151,1376,800,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,800,1709]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Deione renaria n. sp. 1, female habitus, dorsal view; 2, male habitus, dorsal view; 3, left male tibia II, ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195615/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1278,1355,698,724]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1770,1794]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,829,1715]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,791,1748]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Deione ovata n. sp. 10, female habitus, dorsal view; 11, male habitus, dorsal view; 12, left tibia II of male, ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195617/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">10, 11</figureCitation>
). Legs yellowish with dark annuli, tibia II of males expanded with several macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[1094,1170,736,762]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1730,1754]" captionTargetBox="[151,1376,800,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,800,1709]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Deione renaria n. sp. 1, female habitus, dorsal view; 2, male habitus, dorsal view; 3, left male tibia II, ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195615/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1184,1217,736,762]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1770,1794]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,829,1715]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,791,1748]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Deione ovata n. sp. 10, female habitus, dorsal view; 11, male habitus, dorsal view; 12, left tibia II of male, ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195617/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">12</figureCitation>
). Abdomen longer than wide, with pairs of macrosetae anteriorly and two pairs of vertically arranged lateral humps posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[159,266,810,836]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1730,1754]" captionTargetBox="[151,1376,800,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,800,1709]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Deione renaria n. sp. 1, female habitus, dorsal view; 2, male habitus, dorsal view; 3, left male tibia II, ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195615/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[280,355,810,836]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1770,1794]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,829,1715]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,791,1748]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Deione ovata n. sp. 10, female habitus, dorsal view; 11, male habitus, dorsal view; 12, left tibia II of male, ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195617/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">10, 11</figureCitation>
). Epigynum with grooved scape (
<figureCitation box="[754,854,810,836]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,369,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,357,1456]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Deione renaria n. sp. 4, epigynum, ventral view; 5, epigynum, lateral view; 6, vulva, dorsal view; 7, vulva, dorsal view (cleared in lactic acid); 8, left palp, prolateral view; 9, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">
Figs 
<number box="[815,854,810,836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4-7</number>
</figureCitation>
) or scape absent (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1157,810,836]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[169,1408,405,1530]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,381,1558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Deione ovata n. sp. 13, epigynum, ventral view; 14, vulva, dorsal view; 15, left palp, prolateral view; 16, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1125,1157,810,836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
); copulatory ducts long and twisted; spermathecae kidney-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[700,816,848,874]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,369,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,357,1456]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Deione renaria n. sp. 4, epigynum, ventral view; 5, epigynum, lateral view; 6, vulva, dorsal view; 7, vulva, dorsal view (cleared in lactic acid); 8, left palp, prolateral view; 9, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
) or ovoid (
<figureCitation box="[960,1058,848,874]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[169,1408,405,1530]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,381,1558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Deione ovata n. sp. 13, epigynum, ventral view; 14, vulva, dorsal view; 15, left palp, prolateral view; 16, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1022,1058,848,874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male palp with two patellar macrosetae; paracymbium small, basally located (
<figureCitation box="[740,817,885,911]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,369,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,357,1456]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Deione renaria n. sp. 4, epigynum, ventral view; 5, epigynum, lateral view; 6, vulva, dorsal view; 7, vulva, dorsal view (cleared in lactic acid); 8, left palp, prolateral view; 9, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[830,862,885,911]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[169,1408,405,1530]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,381,1558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Deione ovata n. sp. 13, epigynum, ventral view; 14, vulva, dorsal view; 15, left palp, prolateral view; 16, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">16</figureCitation>
); median apophysis foliiform (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1299,885,911]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,369,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,357,1456]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Deione renaria n. sp. 4, epigynum, ventral view; 5, epigynum, lateral view; 6, vulva, dorsal view; 7, vulva, dorsal view (cleared in lactic acid); 8, left palp, prolateral view; 9, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1284,1299,885,911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) or hooked (
<figureCitation box="[160,254,922,948]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[169,1408,405,1530]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,381,1558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Deione ovata n. sp. 13, epigynum, ventral view; 14, vulva, dorsal view; 15, left palp, prolateral view; 16, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[220,254,922,948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="35" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
); conductor membranous (
<figureCitation box="[593,709,922,948]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,369,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,357,1456]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Deione renaria n. sp. 4, epigynum, ventral view; 5, epigynum, lateral view; 6, vulva, dorsal view; 7, vulva, dorsal view (cleared in lactic acid); 8, left palp, prolateral view; 9, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[724,807,922,948]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[169,1408,405,1530]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,381,1558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Deione ovata n. sp. 13, epigynum, ventral view; 14, vulva, dorsal view; 15, left palp, prolateral view; 16, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">15, 16</figureCitation>
); embolus slender and long (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1257,922,948]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,369,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,357,1456]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Deione renaria n. sp. 4, epigynum, ventral view; 5, epigynum, lateral view; 6, vulva, dorsal view; 7, vulva, dorsal view (cleared in lactic acid); 8, left palp, prolateral view; 9, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1272,1306,922,948]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[169,1408,405,1530]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,381,1558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Deione ovata n. sp. 13, epigynum, ventral view; 14, vulva, dorsal view; 15, left palp, prolateral view; 16, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">15</figureCitation>
); terminal apophysis obvious (
<figureCitation box="[383,459,960,986]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,369,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,357,1456]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Deione renaria n. sp. 4, epigynum, ventral view; 5, epigynum, lateral view; 6, vulva, dorsal view; 7, vulva, dorsal view (cleared in lactic acid); 8, left palp, prolateral view; 9, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">Figs 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[472,504,960,986]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[169,1408,405,1530]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,381,1558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Deione ovata n. sp. 13, epigynum, ventral view; 14, vulva, dorsal view; 15, left palp, prolateral view; 16, left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195618/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="35">15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
